    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-29T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-29T03:00:00-05:00" n="439"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d439">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102Ic/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-29T16:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 29, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 22—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>179. My despatch number 45, September 29th, 1921.<note n="30" xml:id="d439fn30">
                        <ref target="frus1921v01#pg_516">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1921, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 516</ref>.</note> On April 26th
                    diplomatic corps, in consequence of movement of Chinese troops in the provinces,
                    reminded Chinese Government of dean’s note August 30, 1921,<note n="31"
                        xml:id="d439fn31">
                        <ref target="frus1921v01#pg_517">
                            <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 517</ref>.</note> and reaffirmed the
                    position that foreign powers will insist that Chinese Government hold higher
                    military authorities personally and individually responsible for damage to
                    foreign interests, by action or failure to act, of their respective troops in
                    territory under their protection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
